# Backend Go ‚Äî source of truth

This rule defines layout and layering for `github.com/MarianC10/connect-office/backend`.

## Layout

```text
backend/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ go.mod
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ docker-compose.yml       # local PostgreSQL (db + init SQL mount)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ db/init/                 # schema applied on first container init (docker-entrypoint-initdb.d)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .env.example             # DATABASE_URL template
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cmd/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ server/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ main.go          # config, wiring, register routes, ListenAndServe ‚Äî no business logic
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ seed/
‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ main.go          # dev data loader (requires DATABASE_URL; truncates seed tables)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ internal/                # not importable by other modules
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <slice>/             # vertical slice (e.g. locations); package name = slice name
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ service.go       # required: use cases, validation, DTO mapping, store calls (no HTTP)
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ handler.go       # HTTP only: decode/bind, call service, write status + JSON
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ models.go        # request/response DTOs (JSON tags, validation tags)
        ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ store.go         # optional: persistence / external APIs (add when needed)
```

## Dependency direction

- **handler** ‚Üí **service**; **service** ‚Üí **store** (when present). Handlers do not call **store** directly.

## Responsibilities

| Layer | Role |
|--------|------|
| **service** | Use cases for the slice: orchestration, rules/validation, mapping to/from DTOs, `context`, calling **store**. Construct `*Service` in `main`, inject into handlers. |
| **handler** | Thin HTTP adapter; call service methods; set headers/status. |
| **models** | API DTOs (`json` tags). Internal working types can live unexported in **service** (or **store**) until a separate domain layer is warranted. |
| **store** | I/O: DB (GORM + Postgres driver), external HTTP clients. Behind small interfaces when testing or swapping backends. |

## `cmd/server`

- Parse configuration, build `*Service` (and stores when they exist), register handlers, start the server.
- Import paths: `github.com/MarianC10/connect-office/backend/internal/<slice>`.

## Database (PostgreSQL)

- Local DB: from `backend/`, `docker compose up -d` (see `docker-compose.yml` and `db/init/`).
- Server and `cmd/seed` expect **`DATABASE_URL`** (see `.env.example`). Schema changes belong in `db/init/` (new numbered `.sql` files) or a future migration tool if you outgrow init scripts.
- **Seed** (`go run ./cmd/seed` from `backend/`) reloads reference data; the current locations seed **truncates** `location_amenities`, `amenities`, and `locations` ‚Äî use only for local/dev.

## Naming

- Do **not** use `package http` for application code (clashes with `net/http`). Use the slice name (`locations`, ‚Ä¶) or names like `httpserver` only for a dedicated router wrapper.

## Cross-slice code

- Shared infrastructure: `internal/platform/` or `internal/pkg/` (logging, DB pool, middleware). Keep generic.
- Avoid a large shared `models` package until several slices need the same DTOs.

## Testing

- Table-test **service** logic with fake stores where I/O is involved.
- **Handlers**: `httptest` for status codes and JSON bodies.

## New slice checklist

1. Add `internal/<slice>/` with `service.go`, `handler.go`, `models.go`, and `store.go` when persistence appears.
2. Wire routes in `cmd/server/main.go` (or `internal/httpserver` if registration outgrows `main`).
